import logging, sys
logging.basicConfig\(level=logging.DEBUG, stream=sys.stdout, format='%\(name\)s: %\(message\)s'\)
for name in ['LiteLLM', 'httpx', 'httpcore', 'openai']:
    logging.getLogger\(name\).setLevel\(logging.ERROR\)

from app.prototype.agents.critic_llm import CriticLLM
from app.prototype.agents.critic_types import CritiqueInput

critic = CriticLLM\(max_escalations=2\)
inp = CritiqueInput\(
    task_id='debug-2', subject='Chinese xieyi mountain', cultural_tradition='chinese_xieyi',
    candidates=[{'candidate_id': 'c1', 'prompt': 'mountain xieyi', 'model_ref': 'flux', 'image_url': None}],
    evidence={'terminology_hits': [{'term': 'xieyi', 'matched': True, 'confidence': 0.9}],
              'sample_matches': [{'id': 's1', 'score': 0.75}], 'taboo_violations': []},
\)
output = critic.run\(inp\)
m = critic.get_agent_metrics\(\)
print\(f'success={output.success} escalations={m["total_escalations"]} tools={m["tool_calls"]}'\)
if output.scored_candidates:
    for ds in output.scored_candidates[0].dimension_scores:
        print\(f'  {ds.dimension}: {ds.score:.4f} | {\(ds.rationale or ""\)[:90]}'\)
PYEOF)

import asyncio, litellm

async def test\(\):
    tools = [
        {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "submit_evaluation", "description": "Submit score", "parameters": {"type": "object", "required": ["score"], "properties": {"score": {"type": "number"}}}}},
        {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "search", "description": "Search", "parameters": {"type": "object", "required": ["query"], "properties": {"query": {"type": "string"}}}}},
    ]
    msgs = [
        {"role": "system", "content": "You are an evaluator."},
        {"role": "user", "content": "Evaluate this artwork."},
    ]
    
    # Test 1: specific function tool_choice
    print\("Test 1: tool_choice = specific function dict"\)
    try:
        resp = await litellm.acompletion\(
            model="deepseek/deepseek-chat",
            messages=msgs,
            tools=tools,
            tool_choice={"type": "function", "function": {"name": "submit_evaluation"}},
            max_tokens=512,
            temperature=0.3,
        \)
        c = resp.choices[0]
        print\(f"  finish={c.finish_reason}, tool_calls={bool\(c.message.tool_calls\)}"\)
        if c.message.tool_calls:
            for tc in c.message.tool_calls:
                print\(f"  -> {tc.function.name}"\)
    except Exception as e:
        print\(f"  ERROR: {e}"\)

asyncio.run\(test\(\)\)
PYEOF)

import asyncio, litellm, json

async def test\(\):
    tools = [
        {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "submit_evaluation", "description": "Submit score", "parameters": {"type": "object", "required": ["score"], "properties": {"score": {"type": "number"}}}}},
        {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "read_layer_analysis", "description": "Read layer analysis", "parameters": {"type": "object", "required": ["layer"], "properties": {"layer": {"type": "string"}}}}},
    ]
    
    # Simulate the multi-turn conversation with tool results
    msgs = [
        {"role": "system", "content": "You are an art critic evaluating L5. Read prior layer analyses with read_layer_analysis. When ready, call submit_evaluation."},
        {"role": "user", "content": "Evaluate Chinese xieyi. Score: [0,1], confidence: [0,1]."},
        # assistant calls read_layer_analysis
        {"role": "assistant", "content": None, "tool_calls": [{"id": "tc1", "type": "function", "function": {"name": "read_layer_analysis", "arguments": '{"layer":"L4"}'}}]},
        {"role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "tc1", "content": '{"layer":"L4","status":"not_yet_evaluated","hint":"No prior analysis. Use other tools or submit."}'},
        # assistant calls read_layer_analysis again
        {"role": "assistant", "content": None, "tool_calls": [{"id": "tc2", "type": "function", "function": {"name": "read_layer_analysis", "arguments": '{"layer":"L3"}'}}]},
        {"role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "tc2", "content": '{"layer":"L3","status":"not_yet_evaluated","hint":"No prior analysis. Use other tools or submit."}'},
    ]
    
    print\("Test: specific function tool_choice with multi-turn history"\)
    tc = {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "submit_evaluation"}}
    resp = await litellm.acompletion\(
        model="deepseek/deepseek-chat",
        messages=msgs,
        tools=tools,
        tool_choice=tc,
        max_tokens=512,
        temperature=0.3,
    \)
    c = resp.choices[0]
    if c.message.tool_calls:
        for t in c.message.tool_calls:
            print\(f"  Called: {t.function.name} args={t.function.arguments[:100]}"\)
    else:
        print\(f"  No tool calls, content={c.message.content[:200] if c.message.content else None}"\)

asyncio.run\(test\(\)\)
PYEOF)
